inn1.comm: bang on target right away, pitches just outside off and moves a shade into Strauss who watches it all the way through to Gilchrist
no movement back into Strauss this time, that pitches just outside off and angles across the left hander who plays back and defends
England are away with a wide, fired down leg side and that bounced a second time before Gilchrist collected it
striahgter line on off stump, pushed on the back foot to cover where Symonds sprints across to pick it up one-handed
a touch fuller in length and one middle and leg stump, Strauss flicks off his pads but can't beat square leg, he really should have pierced the infield
pitches wide outside of stump and angles away from Strauss who lets it go
short of a length outside off stump, Struass cuts off the back foot but straight to point, just the one wide in the over, tidy start by Lee
full and swinging into Bell's pads, clipped to midwicket
beats the outside edge with one that pitches on off stump and moves ever so slightly away from Bell who prodded forward and was comprehensively beaten
fuller ball on the pads, Bell pushes it wide off mid-on for the first runs off the bat
pitches on a good length outside off stump, defended on the front foot back past the bowler
full length on middle stump, a hint of swing back into Strauss, the batsmen plays it to midwicket
shorter in length outside off stump, driven off the back foot to symonds at cover, just the one run  off Bracken's over, the good news for England is that all their wickets are intact
pitches on off and hits Bell on the pad, that couldhave been close but he got  an inside edge on it
defended to midwicket
good length on off stump and it keeps a touch low, it did that a lot in the game between India and England, defended on the front foot
pushed back to Lee on the front foot
no-ball called, full and on off stump, pushed to mid-on, that's the first no-ball of the innings
good length, slanting in to Bell from outside off stump, defended on the off side
in the corridor outside off stump, Bell plays it with an angled bat to point, just the one extra in the over again, Lee hasn't conceded a run off the bat yet
full on off stump, driven firmly on the front foot but mid-off is quick to run across and cut it off
short of a length outside off stump, Strauss tries to cut but gets a thick bottom edge on the off side, they scamper a single
dabbed short of point on the off side for a quick single
full and angling into Strauss from outside off stump, he drives at it but gets a thick outside edge that flies in the air  down to third man

poor ball, too straight and slanting into the pads, Bell closes the face of the bat and times the flick perfectly, more importantly he finds the gap at midwicket and England collect their first boundary
beaten outside the off stump, Bell plays a forward defensive but the ball moves away off the pitch and sneaks past the bat
short of a length and angling into Strauss with the arm, the batsman tries to drive off the back foot but edges it on to his pad
pitches on a good length outside off stump, forced to point on the back foot, no room to play with on that occasion
quick single taken to mid-on, Strauss played that uppishly past the man at short midwicket
short outside off stump, no movement at all for Lee, Bell waits for it and guides it past point and times it superbly for it to reach the fence
defended back to the bowler, Lee gets the line much straighter this time, Bell had no room to play it on the off side
Lee oversteps again, defended back to the bowler
and England pick up four off the extra ball, poor delivery from Lee, a half-volley on the pads, Bell flicks it in the air but in the front of square leg for four
short ball and Strauss gives him the charge straightaway, he pulls it on the front foot through wide mid-on for four
short wide and bang! Strauss cuts fiercely over point and it thuds into the fence, McGrath continues to struggle
pushed on the back foot to cover
fuller in length and Struass takes a step down and drives to mid-on, he is looking to take McGrath on at every opportunity
defended back to the bowler
short of a length on leg and middle stump, Strauss waits for it and closes the face of the bat to play it to midwicket
short of a length outside off stump, that rises on Bell who stands up on the back foot and punches to cover
fuller length on middle stump, defended on the front foot, the pitch so far hasn't showed signs of being a treacherous one
that keeps a little low on off stump, Bell watches it carefully and defends on the back foot
full ball on off stump, Bell drives on the up back to Lee who manages to get his boot in the way to save runs
loose ball, full and drifting on to leg stump, Bell clips it off his pads down to McGrath at long leg
steered backward of point for a single
and McGrath's first ball goes rocketing through midwicket for four again. Bell transfers his weight on the front foot and forces it through midwicket, it was a bit uppish but very safely in the gap
defended solidly on the off side
good length outside off stump, Bell moves forward and plays it with an angled bat to point
poor ball, short and wide outside off, cut down to third man for one
short of a length, angling into Strauss from round the wicket, defended to midwicket, the batsmen are keen to take a step or two down to McGrath
driven uppishly back past McGrath for one, it was mis-timed as well
short of a length, searing into Strauss's off stump, forced off the back foot to Hussey at short cover
the ball isn't coming on to the bat, pitches short of a length and angles into Strauss's hips, defended on the leg side
defended on the off side on the front foot
fuller ball on off stump, Strauss gets on the front foot and plays the cover drive, didn't time it as well as he would have wanted and finds Symonds
short of a length outside off, Strauss forces it off the back foot to point
middle- stump line, that pitches on a good length and Strauss missed it completely as he tried to play it towards midwicket, he gets hit on the pad, Lee finishes a maiden over
shortish length outside off stump, cut hard but straight to point
short ball, it was perhaps the attempted bouncer but it didn't rise at all, Bell waits for it, swivels, and pulls it to deep square leg
slower ball but it was ill-directed, angling into leg stump, Strauss glances it down to fine leg
straighter line on middle stump, Strauss dabs it towards mid-on for a sharp single

Martyn grasses an absolute sitter at mid-off! It was the slower ball and Bell was early on the drive, it lobbed tamely towards Martyn who was back-pedaling to get into position, he looked very awkward when the ball came to him and he fluffed it
worked to midwicket for a single
short of a length, angling across Bell who drives to cover
guided down to third man for one
Gilchrist is standing up to the stumps and Strauss opens the face to run it fine and down to the third-man fence
outside off stump again, Strauss runs it down to third man for one this time
very short ball outside off stump, Bell uses the pace of the ball and delicately cuts past point, he times it well enough to beat third man and that's England's fifty
slanting into the right hander from outside off stump, defended on the off side
McGrath oversteps this time, defended to point
whoops! Strauss gives McGrath the charge and was no where near the pitch of the ball, he tries to loft it down the ground but misses it completely
tucked off his hips down to fine leg, the batsmen called two right from the start and made it comfortably though the throw from the deep was excellent
attempted yorker dug out on the leg side
defended on the off side
short ball and drifting down leg side, Bell tucks it down to long leg, Hussey runs across and makes a full-bodied dive but to no avail as the ball reaches the fence
defended back to the bowler
slanting into the pads, worked through square leg for one
fullish length on off and middle, defended on the back foot
on a good length outside off stump, pushed to point
short of a length outside off stump, played to point
on a good length angling into off stump, defended on the front foot
poor ball, slips way down leg side, Bell should have got a touch on that it would have been a certain four, Gilchrist moves quickily across and collects it
driven firmly to mid-off where Lee dives to his left and saves four runs
worked down to fine leg for two
short and wide outside off, Strauss upper cuts it to third man
good length on off and middle, defended on the back foot
dabbed short of cover on the off side for a quick single
full, fast and a hint of swing back into Strauss who tries to flick but gets hit on the pad
good length outside off  stump and it keeps a touch low, Strauss tries to cut but misses, Gilchrist takes it on the second bounce
full ball on off stump, Bell waits for it and times the drive well, Lee dives to his left at mid-off but can't prevent the single
short of a length outside off stump, Strauss tries to guide it down to third man but he gets beaten
this time he squeezes it down to third man, more of an outside edge really, McGrath runs across and does the fielding just inside the fence
defended on the front foot
played with an angled bat to point
good length, alantng into Strauss who nudges it through midwicket
short of a length on of and middle, Strauss gets an edge on the leg side
no-ball called, nudged on the off side for one
full ball on middle, Strauss tries to force it off his pads but is beaten
short of a length outside off stump, Strauss moves across and forward and tries to play it to square leg, he gets hit on the pad
pitches on off stump and moves away from Bell who tries to run it down to third man but gets beaten
full toss, the yorker gone astray, Bell didn't seem to spot that and plays it to point off an outside edge
good length and slanting across Bell from over the wicket, the batsman drives on the back foot to cover
good length in the corridor outside off stump, Strauss tries to drive on the back foot but gets beaten, England are looking a bit iffy after the drinks break
driven to mid-on for one
shorter in length and angling into Bell from round the wicket, he backs away on the leg side, trying to make room so that he can force it on the off
he backs away again towards leg and dabs the ball towards point for a quick single
guided down to third man from outside off stump
tucked off the pads to short fine leg
classy shot! A tinge of Mahela Jayawardene in that one. He stepped down the track and backed away to make room, it was the slower ball and Bell drove it effortlessly through cover for four
driven off the back foot to mid-off
thumped to mid-off this time, Mratyn runs to his right and dives to cut off a boundary
Bell charges down the track and gets beaten
played with an angled bat down to third man for one
good length on off and middle, driven back to the bowler
fullish length on off stuump, driven on the front foot to Ponting at cover

Watson strikes with his second ball! Bell should have really smashed that for four because it was short and wide outside off stump, instead he drove in the air on the back foot and straight to Hussey at cover
defended on the off side on the front foot
short of a length outside off stump, Pietersen gets his front foot forward and defends away from his body
slower ball, fullish outside off stump, Pietersen drives on the front foot to mid off

short of a length outside off stump, Pietersen drops it short of Clarke at point and sets off for a sharp single, Clarke swoops down on it and fires it in at the non-strikers end, would have been tight had he hit the stumps
banged in short, that rose on Pietersen who was very late in playing it, he tries to fend it of his shoulder and the ball lobs safe on the off side
and the second wicket goes! Johnson bowls the offcutter, it pitches around off stump and moves away from Pietersen who gets drawn into the drive and edges it tamely to Gilchrist
fullish outside off stump, Flintoff tries to drive but gets an edge down to third  man
short of a length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
fuller length on off stump, Strauss drives back to Johnson
excellent, excellent shot! Johnson tries to york Strauss but though he gets his length right, the line is outside off stump, Strauss chops down at it and runs  it fine down to the third-man boundary
defended on the off side
slower ball but also a no-ball, Flintoff tries to drive but isn't to the pitch of the ball, he gets an edge down to third man
another no-ball but this one is quicker, Strauss tries to pull because the ball is short but gets beaten and hit on the pad
wide outside off stump, Strauss guides it down to third man
full length on off stump, Flintoff gets forward and times the drive well to mid-off
short of a length outside off stump, defended on the off side
short ball but it hardly bounces, Flintoff waits for it and pushes it on the front foot to point
pitches on a good length and moves a shade into Flintoff who defends on the off side
pitches around off stump and moves back into Strauss who is beaten for pace and gets hit on the pad, Johnson thinks he has a case for lbw but that was slanting down leg side
defended back to the bowler
he's beaten for pace again, strauss tries to play it on the leg side but gets hit on the pad and goes on the off
short ball and that isn't a very good idea on this pitch unless you're express pace, Strauss is quick to get into position and pulls it to the long-leg fence
defended on the front foot on the off side
good-length ball, pitches on leg and middle, Flintoff defends back to the bowler
good length, angling into Strauss's off stump giving him no room at all, defended on the off side
and again there's no room for Strauss to work with as Lee slants it into his off stump, defended on the back foot back to the bowler
homing in on off stump again but it's a touch shorter this time, punched off the back foot to cover
full ball on off stump, Strauss gets on the front foot and smashes it, Symonds runs in from cover and dives to cut off any runs
fullish again from Lee on off stump, driven to Symonds at cover
Lee finishes the over like he started it, with one that comes into Strauss's off stump, played to point
short of a length, angling across Flintoff from over the wicket, pushed through cover on the front foot for one
angling into Strauss from over the wicket, he tries to flick it off his pads but gets an edge on the leg side, the single brings up England's hundred
defended on the off side on the front foot
full and fast outside off stump, Flintoff throws his weight behind the lofted drive over cover but only manages an edge that flies down to third man
drifting on to middle and leg, tucked off the pads for a single

that missed the outside edge by very little. Johnson pitches it short of a length and moves it across Flintoff from over the wicket, the batsmen prods tentatively at it outside the off stump and is beaten
that wasn;t that short as it slanted into Strauss from round the wicket, the batsman was quick to get into position to pull it through midwicket
Lee replies with a well-directed yorker, dug out on the leg side
a touch short and a fraction outside off stump, Strauss pulls the square drive out of his bag and slams it through point to move on to 49
full, fast and angling into leg stump, Strauss gets beaten for pace and is hit on the pad
pushed on the front foot to midwicket
Strauss backs away to make room and squeezes it past point for a single to bring up his fifty, well played
Starts off with a slanted delivery on the off, swatted away to cover point
fullish and mistimes his drive to widish mid-off

Ouch. Flintoff is hit on the helmet as he loses sight of the ball. He advanced down the wicket and Watson adjusted to it by banging it in short, Flintoff just lost sight as he shaped for a pull and was hit

After being surprised by a bouncer early this over, Flintoff pulled this one to deep midwicket. Banged in short and Flintoff pulled it with neither power nor placement and Hussey ran in a few yards to take the catch.
beaten as he tries to a pull a shortish ball
Walks all over his crease and nearly yorked himself in the process. Manages to dig out a fullish ball towards point.
full in length, on the off stump line, pushed towards mid-off.
again walks a bit around, almost keeps his right leg across and has to get his bat around it to make contact
shuffles across and gets behind a length delivery on the middle and off to block it away
hit the deck short of length and came in from outside the off stump. That shuffle again gets him behind the line and he pushes it to the off side. Lee rushes across to make the stop
on the middle and leg, tucked to left of Symonds at short midwicket
Should have put that one away. short of length and outside off, room was there to free his arms, instead he cut it straight to backward point
dabs to right of backward point - Michael Clarke is the man there- down to thirdman for a single
pushed to cover
all that shuffle, all that effort for nothing. Can't get power behind his forcing stroke. He wanted to peirce the off side field, instead too much bottom hand sends it rolling gently to the on side
pushed back to Symonds
floated up on middle and leg, from round the stumps, swept fine
Dropped! Was it? Tossed up just outside off and Struass goes for a drive, gets an outside edge but Gilchrist can't hold on. Can't be sure whether he got a nick, if TV confirms I shall let you know
beaten, attempted sweep, it turns past him
Symonds and Gilchrist combo works this time. Strauss tries to cut a ball that turned away after landing on the off stump line and ends up nicking it into the gloves
bottom-hand powered square-drive to Hussey at the sweeper cover
Collingwood is away with a typical dab. Nudges a short of length delivery on the stumps through midwicket. Reminds one a lot of the former English batsman, Neil Fairbrother.
tip and run, push to the on side and they go
Collingwood is unable to manouevre this one. A length delivery just outside off stump and he is unable to dab it away.
Should have atleast got a single of this one. Short of length, outside off, cut straight to point
slower one , 115kmph, looped up in front of off stump. Collingwood picked it late and almost stumbled onto it with a forward push to the off side
Really flighted delivery. came in with the angle and Yardy is rapped on the pads. Symonds appeals for a lbw decision but going down may be
paddles a low full-toss to fine-leg
floated on the off stump, driven to long-off
Clarke from short midwicket gets across in time to stop the ball from heading towards long-on. Collingwood had punched it off the back foot.
Collingwood goes over Clarke this time. As if he wants to say - stop this if you can!  He comes down the track and chips it over short midwicket
Yardy gets a tickle. Won't be laughing though. A ball at his ribs sent straight to Gilchrist.
fullish on the legs, tucked behind square-leg
short of length on the middle, pushed back down the track
on the hips, tucked to long-leg
punches a short of length delivery back to bowler
Manages to turn that one for a single. Short of length and on the middle and leg, tucked to right of midwicket
can't do much with that one. on the middle, neither erring in line or length and Darylmple pushes it tamely back to bowler
could have done something with this but ...   outside off and on a driveable length, mistimed drive sends the ball towards cover
Collingwood opens the face of the bat to a length delivery outside off to push it past point and runs hard to come back for the second run.
leans forward to a length delivery on the off stump to push it to cover
banged in short - Watson bowls a quite a few of those, pulled down to the ground, out to deep midwicket
again banged in short but this one was in the zone outside off, swayed away
run down to right of  Bracken at thirdman
length delivery outside off, Collingwood pushes it, in the air, between cover and point
sprayed on the legs, worked past square-leg. If he had got a bit squarer he could have got atleast two, if not four.
comes forward to dead-bat a length delivery ..
slightly short of length, came in after landing just outside the off stump, turned to  short midwicket
cuts a back of length delivery but can't beat Clarke at point
The cut didn't work, neither does a push. Tries to push one to left of Clarke but can't get much pace.
right on target. slanted delivery on the off stump, pushed to cover
well outside the off stump, close to a wide, Collingwood can't quite reach it
on the hips, worked to deep midwicket
hmm ..bounce there. That would make Harmison happy.  Kicked from short of length, chest high and Darymple adjusts to punch it down in front of him
England slip further into trouble. A ordinary delivery on the leg and middle, is pushed in the air towards Ponting at short midwicket. Ponting dives forward and low to grab the catch.
All the twists in the story, after the start, have gone Australia's way. Read decides to join in the procession with a airy waft outside off but doesn't get a touch
pushed to mid-on
runs down the track but can only push it softly to Bracken at mid-on
McGrath guns for the toes, out go Collingwood's front foot in a hurry and the bat comes down quickly to jab the ball away to Ponting at short midwicket
pushes a length delivery towards mid-on but Ponting gets across quickly to make a tumbling stop
with the mid-on now pushed back, Collingwood sends one his way for a single
Read tried it on his first ball but succeeds now. A lame poke at a length delivery in the corridor outside off stump puts an early end to his stay.
Sajid Mahmood almost does a Read. Almost a fatal waft outside off.
push to point. No chance of a run. England have squandered such a good start. Pity.
again the bat is pushed way ahead of his body, well the proper batsmen did it, why not Sajid, outside edge takes the ball to thirdman
Collingwood meanwhile continues to earn his living by dabbing and nudging England out of crisis. A dab to fineleg. But I doubt whether he can slowly push Enlgnad out of trouble today.

Two men dive. A single results.  Mahmood turns a fullish ball on the middle and leg to left of short midwicket. Ponting hurls himself to his left, misses, and Bracken dives to his right and makes the stop. Moral of the stroy; dive right. Arrgh.. need a break I think.
on the hips, turned to fineleg
short of length on the off and middle, pushed back down the track
on the middle and leg, Collingwood turns it behind square-leg and rushes across for a single but his thought of a second is killed as Watson hurtles towards the ball
on the hips, turned to the on side
Another slanted delivery, Mahmood gets squared up a bit but manages to push it towards cover
on the hips, worked past midwicket and they run hard to come back for the second
another slanted delivery, Mahmood pushes at it but gets an inside edge
manages to push this one past point to bring Collingwood on strike
tip and run. Another slanted delivery, slightly short of length, Collingwood taps it gently towards cover point and runs with the stroke
beaten by a shooter outside off stump. Kept low after landing and the tall Mahmood stoops low but can't put bat to ball.
150 up for England. 67 balls for the first fifty but the 101 for the third fifty. On the legs, tapped close to the leg side and away they went
Another one goes down and England are sinking here. Another tame dismissal. Too early into his push-drive and Bracken accepts the offering.
fullish on the off, pushed to mid-off
full and outside off, steered to thirdman
Firm drive but can't beat Symonds at short cover who dives to his left to make the stop.
Harmison pokes at a shortish delivery which reared up at his right shoulder.  Must have been a faint edge - tv replays seem to suggest it might have brushed the sleeves-  is swalowed up by Gilchrist.
banged in short and outside off stump, cut past point.
short of length outside off, pushed to cover point
inside edge gets the ball to fine-leg. He pushed at that one, slightly away from his body
slanted delivery, Collingwood leans forward to tap it cover
Just outside the off stump and he opened the face of the bat to run it through the vacant slip region. Nicely done by Anderson.
short of length, on the stumps, pushed to cover
inside edge brings Anderson another run. He pushed at a length delivery on teh off and middle and the ball runs down behind square-leg
fullish outside off, steered to thirdman
Anderson continues to impress. Picked the slower one well and leant into his cover drive to pick up two runs
Almost a run out. Anderson pushes a fullish ball to short midwicket where Symonds misfields. They set off for a suicidal run but Symonds failed to hit the sticks at the non-striker's end
overpitched and driven to long-on
Anderson is beaten for pace. Even before the ball landed in fact. He backs away to square-leg as the ball is about to land. And then a lame poke as the ball whizzes past the off stump
Doesn't back away this time. Beaten again though. Just outside off.
dab to thirdman gets him off the strike.
firm drive doesn't get Collingwood retain the strike as he hits it straight to Lee
beats Anderson with a fullish delivery that held its line.
This one comes in a touch with the angle and Anderson is beaten again, this time going for a cut
And again. Anderson finds different strokes to evade the ball. This time a square-drive but the ball nestles into Gilchrist's gloves
This time its a cover drive.  Of course Gilchrist has the ball.
This time a jab, a stab to keep away a yorker. Again can't put bat to ball and it whizzes past the blade to Gilchrist
Sorry, Gilchrist doesn't figure on this delivery. Again the yorker beats Anderson's bat but knocks back the off stump.

inn2.comm: on target right away, swings back into Gilchrist from outside off stump, defended on the leg side
fuller length on off stump, driven back to the bowler
dabbed to cover and the batsmen set off for a very risky single, had Dalrymple picked up the ball at cover there could have been a run-out at the striker's end
pitches on a good length on off stump, defended on the back foot
short of a length just outside off stump, Watson has no room to work with so he defends it on the back foot
a touch shorter in length outside off stump, Watson goes on the back foot and punches through the gap at cover, he doesn't time it well enough to reach the fence but they do run three
pitches outside off stump and shapes away from Watson who plays forward defensively but the ball passes the outside edge by a long way
straighter ball on off stump, Watson defends on the front foot
pitches well outside off stump and goes straight through, Watson wants nothing to do with it and shoulders arms
full outside off stump and Mahmood gets that to swing away from the right hander, Watson drives at it but gets a thick edge in the air in the whereabouts of gully if Flintoff had one
angled down leg side and that is the first extra of the innings
full on the pads outside leg, you can't bowl there to a half-decent batsman let alone Gilchrist unless you want to be punished, Gilchrist clips it down to fine leg for four
and again, another poor ball on the pads, guided to fine leg for four more
that's a lucky four, Watson played the forward defensive shot but the ball moved away from him and took the edge down to third man for four
the ball moves away from Watson again and he slashes at it but gets beaten
played wide off point for one
pitches on a good length and on middle stump line, defended back to the bowler
pitches on middle and leg and cuts back into Gilchrist who tries to force it off the pads but doesn't make proper contact, the ball hits the pad off an edge
that's a freebie, full and wide outside off stump, Watson thumps it through cover for four
a touch too straight this time, drifting on to the pads, Gilchrist tucks it down to fine leg
good length and a fraction outside off stump, good tight line this time, Watson defends on the front foot
another poor delivery, speared into the pads down leg side, Watson clips it down to the fine-leg fence with minimum fuss
played with an open face past point for one

and the delay works in England's favour! Mahmood angles it into Gilchrist from round the wicket, Gilchrist plays outside the line and the ball goes through a huge gap between bat and pad and uproots off stump
defended on the off side
a touch shorter in length, outside off stump, driven on the back foot to mid-off
pitches on a good length on off stump as well, Watson gets his foot forward and blocks it
short ball outside off stump, Watson punches off the back foot to cover but can't beat the infield
short again but on middle and off stump, Watson plays back and defends
lovely ball, pitches on the perfect length just outside off and moves a fraction away, Watson pushes forward at it but the ball whizzes past the outside edge, Anderson completes a maiden over
full outside off stump and it swings quite a bit away from Ponting who plants his front foot forward and lets it go
much shorter in length outside off stump, Ponting waits, gets on the back foot and defends to point
full on middle and off stump, swings away from Ponting who angles it wide of Collingwood at point for one
short outside off stump, Watson punches off the back foot and finds the gap at cover
a touch fuller outside off, Watson pushes it to Pietersen at cover for a quick single

and England have their second wicket! Strauss takes a splendid catch at first slip. Ponting drives hard at the ball but a hint of outswing induces a thick edge, Strauss moves low to his right and even though the ball didn't nestle in his palms, he managed to cup it to his chest to complete a safe catch
defended on the front foot
beaten outside the off stump, Anderson is getting the ball to swing away from the  right hander and Watson gets beaten while playing the forward defense
pushed to Flintoff at short cover
and we have a game on! Banged in short, Watson tries to pull but the ball keeps low and crashes into the stumps
short of a length on leg stump, worked off the pad to midwicket
pitches outside off stump and swings away from Hussey who lets it go
short and wide outside off, Martyn has a swish at it but gets beaten, no-ball called for overstepping
poor ball, releases some of the increasing pressure, drifting on to the pads and Martyn flicks it off his hips down to the fine-leg fence
Martyn plays a flashy drive at one outside the off stump, it swings away a touch and flies in the air to where gully should have been
full outside off stump, Hussey plays it to Yardy who is in a fine gully position
that misses Hussey's outside edge by a whisker, the ball carried on with the angle slanting across the left hander, Hussey played inside the line and gets beaten
drifting on to the pads again, worked down to fine leg
full outside the off stump and swinging away from Hussey who shoulders arms
tight line on off stump, pushed on the front foot to mid-off
Ah. Super shot. On the legs, Martyn's blade came ahead of his pads. Blink. Ball is picked from deep midwicket fence
tip and run. Gently tapped to on side and away they go
No screams Hussey after seeing Martyn setting off. A push towards mid-off had interested Martyn
pushed across Hussey who covers his stumps before shouldering his arms
Almost edged behind. Slanted across, a near-fatal poke but the ball has just whizzed past the outside edge.  Lovely bit of bowling.
poor ball, full and on the pads, Martyn clips it off the pads and it would ahve been for if not for a diving save at midwicket
angling into Hussey from round the wicket giving him no room at all, defended back to the bowler
full outside off stump and swinging into Hussey who covers the line and lets it go
again Mahmood angles it into hussey's off stump, pushed out to point on the front foot
no-ball, but that kept very low and took a bottom edge as it went through to Read on the bounce
full on middle and off, defended to mid-on
probing away outside Hussey's off stump, left alone to the wicketkeeper
short and wide outside off, played to point
driven on the front foot to mid-off to bring up the fifty
slower ball on leg stump, Hussey was early on the shot and ends up pushing it to midwicket
angled across the left hander from over the wicket, Hussey lets it go
too straight this time, strays on to the pads, Hussey dabs it around the corner and  runs like Speedy Gonzales for two
defended back to the bowler
slower ball but Mahmood drifts on to the pads again, Martyn waits for it and places it through midwicket with a well-timed flick
angling into Hussey from round the wicket, cramping him for room, defended to point
far too straight, a touch shorter as well, Hussey turns it off his pads to fine leg
short of a length and drifting into Martyn's hips, glanced down to fine leg
wide outside off stump, not testing the batsman at all, left alone through to the wicketkeeper
far better line, angling into off and middle, pitches on a good length as well, Hussey goes back and plays it back to Mahmood
banged in short, a loosner from Harmison, Martyn rocks back and slams it over midwicket for four
drifts on to the pads this time, easy offerings for Martyn who flicks it to the square leg fence
a hat-trick of fours, a half-volley on the pads, Martyn helps him self to another boundary by flicking through midwicket, horrid start again for Harmison
wide outside off stump, Martyn slashes wildly at it but misses
dabbed short of cover for a quick single
pitches on a good length and angles across Hussey who plays it with an angled bat to point
a yorker speared into the blockhole, Martyn does superbly to dig it out to midwicket
pitches on a good length and it's dead straight, Martyn plays back and defends back to Mahmood
full toss at a comfortable height outside off stump, Martyn pushes through cover for an easy boundary, these are all birthday presents for Martyn who turned 35 today
no ball called, defended on the off side on the front foot
fullish on off stump, driven to mid-off
a touch shorter on off and middle stump, Martyn plays on the back foot and pushes it to mid-on
perfect placement, that was a touch outside off stump and Martyn effortlessly smacks it in the tiny gap between point and gully for four
slanting across Hussey from over the wicket, the batsman gets forward and plays it to point
full outside off stump, Hussey gets on to the front foot and drives through cover, Collingwood gives chase and pulls it in just inside the fence
short and wide outside off stump, Martyn says thank you very much and cuts it past point for four to bring up the 50-run partnership
a half-volley on leg stump, Martyn flicks down to the fine leg fence, Anderson makes a valiant dive but replays show that it is indeed a boundary
pushed to cover on the front foot
speared down leg side, wide called, Harmison is having a nightmare

good ball to finish a bad over, short of a length and that rises on Martyn who drops it at his feet for a quick single, Hussey is far to quick for the fielder at cover who picks up and hits the stumps
pushed through quickly outside off stump, Martyn gets forward and plays it to cover for one
defended  on the off side
angling into the left hander from over the wicket, defended on the leg side
worked down to third man for one
short and wide outside off stump, Martyn leans back and cuts but can't beat short third man
fuller length outside off stump, played with an open face to short third man
full outside off stump, driven to mid-off

Collingwood drops it at point! Short and wide from Anderson, Martyn tries to cut but doesn't get enough elevation, Collingwood had to jump up high at point, he did manage to get two hands to it but couldn't hang on
full on the pads, that should have been punished but Hussey hits it to midwicket
driven to cover on the front foot
slanting across Hussey from over the wicket, left alone outside off
a touch straighter this time, Hussey glances it behind square on the off side but doesn't beat point
fired into the pads, Martyn was beaten by the pace on that ball
defended on the off side on the front foot
fifty for Martyn, he tucks one on his pads down to fine leg to reach the land mark, he's got to fifty of just 35 balls, an invaluable innings when Australia had lost three wickets for four runs
defended on the leg side
played back to the bowler on the front foot
worked through point for a single
good length adn homing in of off stump, Martyn gets forward and blocks it on the off side
short of a length on off stump, Martyn goes on the back foot and defends back down the pitch
drifts down leg side, umpire Billy Bowden says that's wide, the extra brings up Australia's 100
slips down leg side again, another wide, Anderson is on a hat-trick
he nearly had it, fired down leg again, Martyn clips it off his pads down to fine leg for one
pitches outside off stump and moves away from Hussey who lets it go
pitches very wide outside off stump, that was close to being called again
much straighter, on off stump, Hussey plays back and defends
angling into Martyn's middle stump from round the wicket, defended on the front foot
touch fuller on middle stump, driven down the ground for one
defended on the off side
tossed up slower though the air, no turn at all, defended to cover on the front foot
driven to cover
the ball does nothing off the pitch but slant into Martyn with the angle, pushed to cover on the front foot
short of a length, angling across Hussey after pitching on leg and middle, played to point
fuller ball on middle and leg, Hussey gets forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
another wide down leg side, Read collects it on the second bounce
a touch shorter and angling into middle and leg, tucked off the pads through midwicket
short and wide outside off stump, Hussey guides it down to third man
a touch short outside off stump, Hussey tries to cut but gets a thick bottom edge
fuller ball, angling into Hussey from round the wicket, Hussey watches it all the way on to his bat
full and a touch wide outside off stump, driven to sweeper for a single
angling into Hussey from over the wicket, flicked off the pads to square leg
defended back to the bowler
quicker ball pushed through on off stump, defended on the leg side
driven back down the ground
played to short midwicket on the front foot
whoops, that beat everything, Martyn's outside edge and Chris Read, four byes conceded
angling into the pads, Martyn closes the face and plays it to midwicket
short in length and on leg stump, Martyn glances it down to fine leg
short of a length on off and middle, played to midwicket on the back foot
pushed off the back foot to cover
pitches outside off and it spins back into Martyn - first time we've seen that in this innings - who cuts but can't beat short third man
pushed through on off stump, Hussey dabs it on the off side and wants the single but Martyn sends him back
defended on the leg side
flat trajectory on middle stump, defended to midwicket
pushed down the ground on the front foot for a single
angling into off stump, Martyn gets forward and defends
short of a length outside of stump, angling into Hussey who pushes it to mid-on for one, Harmison is slow to react
driven through point for one
on off stump, dabbed in front of point for one
played to point on the back foot for one
pushed to point on the back foot
swept down to fine leg for another single, australia are picking these runs off with ease
slipping on the legs, tickled around the corner.
coming in with the angle from outside off, steered to right of backward point
again drifting in, Martyn backs away to cut to the left of backward point where Bell hurls himself to make the stop
fuller, driven to extra cover
just outside off, no threat of any spin, steered to Bell
Cut to left of Bell. Drifts in from outside off, bit of width, Martyn eases it past backward point.
low full-toss, pushed to cover
length delivery, coming in from outside off, Hussey leans forward to push it towards mid-off
partly-edged, partly-steered past second slip. Short of length delivery, outside off and Hussey hung his bat out with a slightly opened face.
banged in short outside off, Martyn just put his bat out, away from his body, to steer it to point
in the zone outside off, left alone.
pushed wide of the off stump, full in length, Martyn reaches out for it, taps it close to the stumps and hurries across for a quick single. Mahmood goes across to pick the ball.
floated in on the off stump line, pushed back down the track
slightly slower and held back the length a bit, Martyn waited before he turned it to midwicket
again comes in with the angle from outside off - Yardy's stock delivery to a right-hand bat - pushed past cover point
outside off, left alone
appeal for lbw. Almost apolegtic.came in a touch from outside off - so he can turn it the conventional way - and Hussey is rapped on the pads, outside the line, as he pushes forward in defense
bumper. Martyn smelled the perfume ball as he swayed away quickly. Right over the middle, head high and Martyn dropped his wrists and let it go through
length delivery outside off, steered to point
near-fatal slash outside off. Back of a length delivery and well outisde off.
much fuller and closer to the off stump, pushed to short cover
Went for the bouncer. Not a bad idea but ended up pushing it down the legside.
quick single taken. It was speared in on a length outside the off stump, Martyn got a inside edge of a attempted cut and the ball rolled towards Chris Read.
in the channel outside off, Hussey leans forward and watches it all the way into Read's gloves
on the middle and leg, turned to short midwicket
slightly short and comes in from outside off, pushed back down the track
just outside off, steered to backward point
Martyn goes for a cover drive, almost pierces the ring but a neat little diving stop just gives him a run
pushed that one through quicker and flatter on the off stump line, defended away off the front foot

Martyn pings the thirdman fence to bring up the 100 of the partnership. Definite effort to finish it off and up the run rate. Could come handy later on. Slightly short and outside off, Martyn backed away to slash it past backward point
on the middle and leg, turned past midwicket&
speared in on the hips, attempted flick shot fails but the ball runs off the pads past the diving Read
thwack! Overpitched outside off, driven past cover. Almost inside-out.
just short of driveable length, outside the off stump, pushed to right of cover
another one that comes in with the arm, Martyn late-cuts it but can't beat the short thirdman
on the middle and off, turned to midwicket
slightly slower , on the off and middle, pushed to cover
flatter and quicker, outside off, steered to short thirdman
fullish and on the off, Martyn brings his bat down at the last minute- perhaps he was thinking of late-cutting it initially- to push it towards point
shorter and outside off, Martyn backs away to cut it to right of point
But starts off with one drifting down the legside, flicked away fine.
just outside off, steered to left of Collingwood at backward point and by the time he gets across to it, they cross over
fullish and on the off stump line, pushed to left of mid-off
fullish again, driven to mid-off
overpitched on the off and middle, punched back down the track
slower one, 111.9 kmph, outside off but Hussey had picked it, waits for it to arrive before tapping it towards thirdman
flat outside off, pushed away without any power
slightly shorter, punched straight to cover
touch outside off stump, steered to point
fuller and flatter, Hussey presses forward in defense, gets an outside edge to the thirdman region
defended off the front foot.
Finally, after bowling lots of trash, Harmison gets one to kick up from short of length. Martyn tries to help it on his way but nicks it to Read.
back to rubbish. Short and wide outside off, cut past point
fuller and on the off stump, pushed to mid-off
just short of driveable length outside off, steered to point
banged in short, at the body of Symonds who pushes it to close on the legside
slower ball, on the middle, Hussey leans forward to dead-bat it away.
short of length, turns in, turned to short fine-leg
turns in from outside off, Symonds is rapped on the pads as he pushes forward in defense. But point of impact outside off.
paddled away past short fine-leg
slower and on the stumps, worked to midwicket
outside leg, full in length, Hussey goes for a sweep but doesn't make contact and it runs off the pads
long hop but Hussey is no mood for murder.  Pushes it non-violently past cover.
kicks up a bit from back of length, outside off, Symond arches back his upper body, taps it to thirdman
A pull shot but played down to the ground. Short and on the body, pulled to longleg
another one banged in short, it sails over Symonds, who ducks, and bounces once before reaching Read
on the hips, turned past square-leg
glanced fine. Full and drifting on to the legs, tickled around the corner.
Harmison helps with a no ball and Hussey pings the extra cover fence. The no ball would go into the scorecard, the four won't. Anyways Australia have won the battle on the diwali day.
